            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">RSC Lot 60–D 224, Box 96: U.S. Cr. Min. 13</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minutes of the Thirteenth Meeting of the United States
                        Delegation, Held at San Francisco, Monday, April 23, 1945, 11 a.m.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1945-04-23T11:00:00-07:00">April 23, 1945, 11 a.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>[Here follows list of names of persons (17) present at meeting.]</p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary’s Speech at Opening Session</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Senator <persName corresp="#p_VAH1">Vandenberg</persName>
                    </hi> opened the meeting at 11:00 a.m. and asked Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PL1"
                        >Pasvolsky</persName> what the business of the day would be.</p>
                <p>[Here follows summary of discussion of draft text of the Secretary’s speech to be
                    made at the opening session and procedural matters such as agenda of meeting,
                    list of deferred questions, trusteeship <pb facs="0423" n="361" xml:id="pg_361"
                    /> paper drafted on the train, a paper presenting official proposals by other
                    Governments, time of next meetings, distribution of documents, and conference
                    procedures.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
